Genetic Algorithms, Reinforcement Learning. 

Genetic Algorithms are present in the text as the paper discusses experiments on adding memory to XCS, which is a type of classifier system that uses genetic algorithms to evolve rules. The paper explores the effects of adding memory to XCS and how it affects the performance of the system.

Reinforcement Learning is also present in the text as XCS is a type of reinforcement learning algorithm that uses a reward signal to learn optimal behavior. The paper discusses how adding memory to XCS can improve its ability to learn and adapt to changing environments.
